schema.description: [Core] Represents a relationship between a contact and one or more accounts.

Id.title: Account Contact Relationship ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Roles.title: Roles
Roles.description: The contact’s participating role in the account. Values are Business User, Decision Maker, Economic Buyer, Economic Decision Maker, Evaluator, Executive Sponsor, Influencer, Technical Buyer, and Other.

IsDirect.title: Direct
IsDirect.description: Indicates whether the account associated with the contact is the contact's primary account (true) or not (false).

IsActive.title: Active
IsActive.description: Indicates whether relationship is active (true) or not (false).

StartDate.title: Start Date
StartDate.description: The date a relationship between a contact and account began. Use with the End Date to keep a history of the relationship.

EndDate.title: End Date
EndDate.description: The date a relationship between a contact and account ended. Use with the Start Date to keep a history of the relationship.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

If the account has a record type of Person Account: This value is the concatenation of the FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix of the associated person contact. You can't modify this value.

Type.title: Account Type
Type.description: Type of account, for example, Customer, Competitor, or Partner.

ShippingStreet.description: The compound form of the shipping address. Read-only. See Address Compound Fields for details on compound address fields.

ShippingCity.title: Shipping City
ShippingCity.description: The compound form of the shipping address. Read-only. See Address Compound Fields for details on compound address fields.

ShippingState.title: Shipping State/Province
ShippingState.description: The compound form of the shipping address. Read-only. See Address Compound Fields for details on compound address fields.

ShippingPostalCode.title: Shipping Zip/Postal Code
ShippingPostalCode.description: The compound form of the shipping address. Read-only. See Address Compound Fields for details on compound address fields.

ShippingCountry.title: Shipping Country
ShippingCountry.description: The compound form of the shipping address. Read-only. See Address Compound Fields for details on compound address fields.

ShippingLatitude.title: Shipping Latitude
ShippingLatitude.description: The compound form of the shipping address. Read-only. See Address Compound Fields for details on compound address fields.

ShippingLongitude.title: Shipping Longitude
ShippingLongitude.description: The compound form of the shipping address. Read-only. See Address Compound Fields for details on compound address fields.

ShippingGeocodeAccuracy.title: Shipping Geocode Accuracy
ShippingGeocodeAccuracy.description: The compound form of the shipping address. Read-only. See Address Compound Fields for details on compound address fields.

ShippingAddress.title: Shipping Address
ShippingAddress.description: The compound form of the shipping address. Read-only. See Address Compound Fields for details on compound address fields.

Phone.title: Account Phone
Phone.description: Phone number for this account. Maximum size is 40 characters.

AccountNumber.title: Account Number
AccountNumber.description: Account number assigned to this account (not the unique, system-generated ID assigned during creation). Maximum size is 40 characters.

Website.title: Website
Website.description: The website of this account. Maximum of 255 characters.

PhotoUrl.title: Photo URL
PhotoUrl.description: Generate a URL to request the social network profile image associated with the account.

Sic.title: SIC Code
Sic.description: Standard Industrial Classification code of the company’s main business categorization, for example, 57340 for Electronics. Maximum of 20 characters. This field is available on business accounts, not person accounts.

Industry.title: Industry
Industry.description: An industry associated with this account. For example, Biotechnology. Maximum size is 40 characters.

AnnualRevenue.title: Annual Revenue
AnnualRevenue.description: Estimated annual revenue of the account.

NumberOfEmployees.title: Employees
NumberOfEmployees.description: Label is Employees. Number of employees working at the company represented by this account. Maximum size is eight digits.

Ownership.title: Ownership
Ownership.description: Ownership type for the account, for example Private, Public, or Subsidiary.

TickerSymbol.title: Ticker Symbol
TickerSymbol.description: The stock market symbol for this account. Maximum of 20 characters. This field is available on business accounts, not person accounts.

Description.title: Account Description
Description.description: Text description of the account. Limited to 32,000 KB.

Rating.title: Account Rating
Rating.description: The account’s prospect rating, for example Hot, Warm, or Cold.

Site.title: Account Site
Site.description: Name of the account’s location, for example Headquarters or London. Label is Account Site. Maximum of 80 characters.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

LastActivityDate.title: Last Activity
LastActivityDate.description: Value is one of the following, whichever is the most recent: Due date of the most recent event logged against the record. Due date of the most recently closed task associated with the record.

Jigsaw.title: Data.com Key
Jigsaw.description: References the ID of a company in Data.com. If an account has a value in this field, it means that the account was imported from Data.com. If the field value is null, the account was not imported from Data.com. Maximum size is 20 characters. Available in API version 22.0 and later. Label is Data.com Key. This field is available on business accounts, not person accounts. Important The Jigsaw field is exposed in the API to support troubleshooting for import errors and reimporting of corrected data. Do not modify the value in the Jigsaw field.

AccountSource.title: Account Source
AccountSource.description: The source of the account record. For example, Advertisement or Trade Show. The source is selected from a picklist of available values, which are set by an administrator. Each picklist value can have up to 40 characters.

SicDesc.title: SIC Description
SicDesc.description: A brief description of an org’s line of business, based on its SIC code. Maximum length is 80 characters. This field is available on business accounts, not person accounts.

Fax.title: Business Fax

MobilePhone.title: Mobile Phone
MobilePhone.description: Contact’s mobile phone number. Label is Mobile Phone.

HomePhone.title: Home Phone
HomePhone.description: The contact’s home phone number. Label is Home Phone.

AssistantPhone.title: Asst. Phone
AssistantPhone.description: The assistant’s phone number. Label is Asst. Phone.

Title.title: Title

LeadSource.title: Lead Source
LeadSource.description: The source of the lead that was converted to this contact.

Birthdate.title: Birthdate
Birthdate.description: The contact’s birthdate.Filter criteria for report filters, list view filters, and SOQL queries ignore the year portion of the Birthdate field. For example, this SOQL query returns contacts with birthdays later in the year than today:SELECT Name, Birthdate FROM Contact WHERE Birthdate > TODAY

Description.title: Contact Description
Description.description: A description of the contact. Label is Contact Description up to 32 KB.

HasOptedOutOfEmail.title: Email Opt Out
HasOptedOutOfEmail.description: Indicates whether the contact doesn’t want to receive email from Salesforce (true) or does (false). Label is Email Opt Out.

HasOptedOutOfFax.title: Fax Opt Out
HasOptedOutOfFax.description: Indicates whether the contact prohibits receiving faxes.

DoNotCall.title: Do Not Call
DoNotCall.description: Indicates that the contact doesn’t want to receive calls.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

LastActivityDate.title: Last Activity
LastActivityDate.description: Value is the most recent of either: Due date of the most recent event logged against the record. Due date of the most recently closed task associated with the record.

EmailBouncedReason.title: Email Bounced Reason
EmailBouncedReason.description: If bounce management is activated and an email sent to the contact bounces, the reason for the bounce.

EmailBouncedDate.title: Email Bounced Date
EmailBouncedDate.description: If bounce management is activated and an email sent to the contact bounces, the date and time of the bounce.

IsEmailBounced.title: Is Email Bounced
IsEmailBounced.description: If bounce management is activated and an email is sent to a contact, indicates whether the email bounced (true) or not (false).

Jigsaw.title: Data.com Key
Jigsaw.description: References the company’s ID in Data.com. If an account has a value in this field, it means that the account was imported from Data.com. If the field value is null, the account wasn’t imported from Data.com. Maximum size is 20 characters. Available in API version 22.0 and later. Label is Data.com Key. Important The Jigsaw field is exposed in the API to support troubleshooting for import errors and reimporting of corrected data. Do not modify this value.

Pronouns.title: Pronouns
Pronouns.description: The contact’s personal pronouns, reflecting their gender identity. Others can use these pronouns to refer to the contact in the third person. The entry is selected from a picklist of available values, which the administrator sets. Maximum 40 characters.

GenderIdentity.title: Gender Identity
GenderIdentity.description: The contact’s internal experience of their gender, which may or may not correspond to their designated sex at birth.

CreatedDate__c.title: Date ajout
CreatedDate__c.description: Date and time when this record was created.

schema.description: [Core] Represents a warehouse, service vehicle, work site, or other element of the region where your team performs field service work. In API version 49.0 and later, you can associate activities with specific locations. Activities, such as the tasks and events related to a location, appear in the activities timeline when you view the location detail page. Also in API version 49.0 and later, Work.com users can view Employees as a related list on Location records. In API version 51.0 and later, this object is available for Omnichannel Inventory and represents physical locations where inventory is available for fulfilling orders.

Id.title: Location ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Name.title: Location Name
Name.description: The name of the location. For example, Service Van #4.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

LocationType.title: Location Type
LocationType.description: Picklist of location types. It has no default values, so you must populate it before creating any location records.

Description.title: Description
Description.description: A brief description of the location.

PossessionDate.title: Possession Date
PossessionDate.description: The date the location was purchased.

ConstructionStartDate.title: Construction Start Date
ConstructionStartDate.description: Date construction began at the location.

ConstructionEndDate.title: Construction End Date
ConstructionEndDate.description: Date construction ended at the location.

OpenDate.title: Open Date
OpenDate.description: Date the location opened or came into service.

CloseDate.title: Close Date
CloseDate.description: Date the location closed or went out of service.

RemodelStartDate.title: Remodel Start Date
RemodelStartDate.description: Date when remodel construction started at the location.

RemodelEndDate.title: Remodel End Date
RemodelEndDate.description: Date when remodel construction ended at the location.

IsMobile.title: Mobile Location
IsMobile.description: Indicates whether the location moves. For example, a truck or tool box.

IsInventoryLocation.title: Inventory Location
IsInventoryLocation.description: Indicates whether the location stores parts. Note This field must be selected if you want to associate the location with product items.

LocationLevel.title: Location Level
LocationLevel.description: The location’s position in a location hierarchy. If the location has no parent or child locations, its level is 1. Locations that belong to a hierarchy have a level of 1 for the root location, 2 for the child locations of the root location, 3 for their children, and so forth.
